{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781757829501,"sessionID":"ses_126f83aa0ffeGn1t6D6Ful5ZsW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_huyUVcN0GGmdYPDq23cwIwX4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"loadLabeledSet|confidence-labeled-set\\.starter|confidence-calibration-model|SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public","include":"*.{ts,js,mjs,json,md}"},"output":"Found 53 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:\n  Line 17: // default (SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION) and only applies a model when\n\n  Line 73: export function loadLabeledSet(json: unknown): LabeledPair[] {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts:\n  Line 619:  * AND SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL points at a readable model file.\n\n  Line 620:  * Set SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION=true to enable once a validated set exists.\n\n  Line 623:   return isOptInEnabled('SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION');\n\n  Line 642:   const raw = process.env.SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL?.trim();\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/confidence-calibration.vitest.ts:\n  Line 17:   loadLabeledSet,\n\n  Line 24: const FLAG = 'SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION';\n\n  Line 25: const MODEL_PATH_VAR = 'SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL';\n\n  Line 202: describe('loadLabeledSet()', () => {\n\n  Line 204:     const pairs = loadLabeledSet([\n\n  Line 213:     expect(() => loadLabeledSet({} as unknown)).toThrow();\n\n  Line 217:     expect(() => loadLabeledSet([{ query: '', memoryId: 1, relevant: 1 }])).toThrow();\n\n  Line 218:     expect(() => loadLabeledSet([{ query: 'q', memoryId: null, relevant: 1 }])).toThrow();\n\n  Line 219:     expect(() => loadLabeledSet([{ query: 'q', memoryId: 1, relevant: 2 }])).toThrow();\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-opus/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 25: - `loadLabeledSet` rejects malformed entries loudly rather than coercing [SOURCE: confidence-calibration.ts:73-96] — but it is an offline tooling path, not the request hot path.\n\n  Line 26: - Model path comes from an operator-set env var (`SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL`), trimmed and presence-checked [SOURCE: search-flags.ts:640-644]. No untrusted-input path traversal, no credential exposure, no injection surface.\n\n  Line 44: - **Starter model bloat (F002, P2).** The PAV implementation only merges on a strict `prev.meanY > curr.meanY` violation [SOURCE: confidence-calibration.ts:166-175]; adjacent blocks with *equal* means are never pooled. On the perfectly-separable proxy data this yields 100 serialized points for what is effectively a 2-level step (`y=0` until x≈0.27, then `y=1`) [SOURCE: confidence-calibration-model.starter.json:3-404]. Harmless (default OFF, apply handles duplicate-x) but wasteful; the model is also a near-degenerate hard threshold, which corroborates the \"UNVALIDATED proxy — do not enable\" labeling rather than contradicting it.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-opus/deep-review-findings-registry.json:\n  Line 26:         \".../004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-calibration-model.starter.json:3-404\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-opus/deep-review-strategy.md:\n  Line 23: | `004-…/assets/confidence-calibration-model.starter.json` | Demo isotonic model | read |\n\n  Line 47: - Calibration deliverable (B) is flag-gated, default OFF (`SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` via `isOptInEnabled`) and additionally requires a readable model path — confirmed inert in production.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-opus/review-report.md:\n  Line 19: The **code** in this packet is sound and ships safely. The default-ON weight rebalance (`0.45` heuristic / `0.55` absolute-relevance prior) is bounded, clamps to `[0,1]`, and is monotonic in relevance as designed. The calibration infrastructure (B) is genuinely inert in production: it is gated behind the opt-in `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` flag (`isOptInEnabled`, default OFF) **and** an explicit readable model path, with a no-op identity fallback — verified by direct read and by the two wiring tests. The isotonic PAV fit and `applyCalibration` are monotonic and bounded; loaders fail safe (null on bad input in the hot path, loud on malformed labeled sets offline). No P0 and no security findings.\n\n  Line 34: | F002 | P2 | maintainability | Isotonic fit never merges equal-mean adjacent blocks → 100-point starter model for an effective 2-level step | confidence-calibration.ts:163-183 · confidence-calibration-model.starter.json:3-404 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-mimo/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 39: ### P2-001: No test for boolean `relevant` values in `loadLabeledSet()`\n\n  Line 46: `loadLabeledSet()` validates `relevant !== 0 && relevant !== 1` (strict equality), which correctly rejects booleans (`true`/`false`), strings (`\"1\"`), and out-of-range numbers. The validation logic is correct. However, the test suite does not cover the boolean edge case — `loadLabeledSet([{ query: 'q', memoryId: 1, relevant: true }])` is not tested. Adding this case would guard against a future refactor that loosens the check (e.g., `== 0` instead of `=== 0`).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-mimo/deep-review-dashboard.md:\n  Line 36: | P2-001 | P2 | correctness | No boolean test for `loadLabeledSet()` |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-mimo/deep-review-findings-registry.json:\n  Line 22:       \"description\": \"No test for boolean relevant values in loadLabeledSet()\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-mimo/deep-review-strategy.md:\n  Line 12: | `004-…/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json` | 100-pair proxy labeled set | Not reviewed |\n\n  Line 13: | `004-…/assets/confidence-calibration-model.starter.json` | Demo isotonic model | Not reviewed |\n\n  Line 46: | P2-001 | P2 | correctness | No test for boolean `relevant` values in `loadLabeledSet()` | vitest.ts:122-127 | 1 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/review/lineages/p017c004-mimo/review-report.md:\n  Line 47: ### P2-001: No test for boolean `relevant` values in `loadLabeledSet()`\n\n  Line 57: The validation logic correctly rejects booleans (`relevant !== 0 && relevant !== 1`), but no test covers this case. Adding `loadLabeledSet([{ query: 'q', memoryId: 1, relevant: true }])` to the rejection tests would guard against future refactors loosening the check.\n\n  Line 102: 3. **REQ-003**: Flag gating — `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` (default OFF), `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL` path, both-must-be-present contract\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 138: 1. **S4 calibration is unvalidated.** The shipped model is a corpus-derived proxy. It stays default-OFF (`SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION`) until refit on ~50-100 human-judged `memory_search` pairs.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:\n  Line 6: //   - confidence-labeled-set.starter.json   ({query, memoryId, relevant}[])\n\n  Line 7: //   - confidence-calibration-model.starter.json   (fitted isotonic model)\n\n  Line 165: const labeledPath = join(HERE, 'confidence-labeled-set.starter.json');\n\n  Line 166: const modelPath = join(HERE, 'confidence-calibration-model.starter.json');\n\n  Line 189:         'UNVALIDATED: fitted from a keyword-overlap PROXY rawValue, not real pipeline cosine confidence. Demonstrates the fit/apply pipeline only. Do NOT wire as a production model (SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION stays OFF) until refit from live labeled traffic.',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-calibration-model.starter.json:\n  Line 406:   \"_note\": \"UNVALIDATED: fitted from a keyword-overlap PROXY rawValue, not real pipeline cosine confidence. Demonstrates the fit/apply pipeline only. Do NOT wire as a production model (SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION stays OFF) until refit from live labeled traffic.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/spec.md:\n  Line 78: - **(B) flag-gated default-OFF, UNVALIDATED**: isotonic (PAV) `fitCalibration`/`applyCalibration`, a labeled-set loader, and a model file loader, mapped through only when `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` is ON and a readable model is configured - otherwise a no-op.\n\n  Line 119: | `004-…/assets/{fit-calibration.mjs, confidence-labeled-set.starter.json, confidence-calibration-model.starter.json}` | Create | (B) proxy seed generator + 100-pair proxy set + demo model |\n\n  Line 137: | REQ-002 | (B) Calibration infra must be a no-op in production | Default-OFF unless `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` ON AND a readable model is configured; wiring-guarantee test |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 73: New `confidence-calibration.ts` provides an isotonic (PAV) `fitCalibration(samples) → CalibrationModel`, `applyCalibration(model, rawValue) → calibratedValue` (piecewise-linear, monotonic, bounded 0–1), a `loadLabeledSet(json)` validator for `{query, memoryId, relevant}[]`, and a `loadCalibrationModel(path)` file loader. `confidence-scoring.ts` maps `value` through the fitted model **only** when `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` is ON **and** `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL` points at a readable model — otherwise it is a no-op, so production confidence is the rebalance-only value.\n\n  Line 86: | `004-…/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json` | Created | (B) 100-pair proxy labeled set (50 docs) |\n\n  Line 87: | `004-…/assets/confidence-calibration-model.starter.json` | Created | (B) demo isotonic model fit from the proxy |\n\n  Line 148: 1. **The calibration model is UNVALIDATED.** Deliverable (B) is machinery plus a corpus-derived proxy seed. The starter model is fit from keyword-overlap, not real pipeline cosine confidence. It is NOT production-ready and must stay behind `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` (default OFF). Do not enable it against the starter model.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/changelog/002-memory-store-and-search/changelog-002-017-004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set.md:\n  Line 28: - `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` opt-in flag (default OFF) and `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL` model-path resolution\n\n  Line 57: | `…/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json` | Added |\n\n  Line 58: | `…/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-calibration-model.starter.json` | Added |\n\n  Line 63: - The real labeled set (roughly fifty to one hundred human-judged pairs from live `memory_search` traffic, joined to the raw score the pipeline assigned each pair) is the documented prerequisite before `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` can be enabled.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-search-intelligence/008-retrieval-evaluation/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:\n  Line 6: `confidence-calibration.ts` ships a complete isotonic PAV `fitCalibration` (:145), `applyCalibration` (:196), model loader (:104), labeled-set loader (:73). Apply hook = `maybeCalibrate()` (`confidence-scoring.ts:187-192`), double-gated by `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` (opt-in, default-OFF) **AND** `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION_MODEL` (model-JSON path). **`fitCalibration` has ZERO callers outside its vitest.** No proxy-seed JSON, no generator, no fit pipeline exist — the \"proxy seed\" is **conceptual only** (correction to §13).\n\n  Line 10: 2. **A2-C2-GRADE-BINARIZE → NET-NEW (M/S).** Every label surface is graded 0-3 (`GroundTruthRelevance`, `LlmJudgeLabel`, `ManualLabel`) but `CalibrationSample.relevant` is binary 0|1 and `loadLabeledSet` *rejects* non-binary (`confidence-calibration.ts:91`). Design: binarize grade≥2→1 (aligns with the judge's overlap≥0.25→grade-2 band). 110 queries × ~5-10 results = 550-1100 pairs — well above the ~50-100 floor.\n","metadata":{"matches":53,"truncated":false},"title":"loadLabeledSet|confidence-labeled-set\\.starter|confidence-calibration-model|SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION","time":{"start":1781757828986,"end":1781757829499}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_040ec3f5c6aab830016a337784e0c88191a15202c2228fa314"}},"id":"prt_ed90adf62001Np8NEHSyZBnsH0","sessionID":"ses_126f83aa0ffeGn1t6D6Ful5ZsW","messageID":"msg_ed90a7f3d001ryFZQCvs5rivYM"}}
